00:34:43,084 --> 00:34:44,686
- [Sandra] Wait, my left foot.

527
00:34:44,686 --> 00:34:46,769
- [Both] One, two, three.

528
00:34:48,378 --> 00:34:50,398
- [Sandra] Oh, oh my.

529
00:34:50,398 --> 00:34:51,231
- [Tommy] You all right?

530
00:34:51,231 --> 00:34:52,064
(Sandra thuds)

531
00:34:52,064 --> 00:34:53,318
- [Sandra] Oh!

532
00:34:53,318 --> 00:34:54,818
- You okay?
- Yeah.

533
00:34:57,463 --> 00:34:59,103
- [Tommy] All right, here, take this,

534
00:34:59,103 --> 00:35:01,933
meet me around the side, open up the door.

535
00:35:20,285 --> 00:35:21,702
- [Sandra] Tommy.

536
00:35:25,750 --> 00:35:29,000
(tense dramatic music)

537
00:35:44,833 --> 00:35:45,666
- Sandra.

538
00:35:50,871 --> 00:35:51,704
Get down.

539
00:36:37,039 --> 00:36:39,289
(clanking)

540
00:37:11,005 --> 00:37:13,422
(door thuds)

541
00:37:56,200 --> 00:37:57,822
- [Sandra] I'm going with ya.

542
00:37:57,822 --> 00:37:59,833
- No, too risky.

543
00:38:03,600 --> 00:38:06,030
- How can it be risky
if you trust the guy?

544
00:38:06,030 --> 00:38:08,230
- Yeah, well, but what
if he is one of them?

545
00:38:09,110 --> 00:38:10,910
No reason for us both to get burned.

546
00:38:18,190 --> 00:38:20,093
- [Sandra] Shane, what are you doing up?

547
00:38:21,830 --> 00:38:23,320
- What's in the bag?

548
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:25,223
- Nothin', go on, get back to bed.

549
00:38:27,940 --> 00:38:29,730
- Where'd you get it from?

550
00:38:29,730 --> 00:38:30,823
- Back to bed, Shane.

551
00:38:32,860 --> 00:38:34,910
- Shane, the only thing
that you have to know

552
00:38:36,863 --> 00:38:39,293
is that I'd never let
anything happen to your mom.

553
00:38:40,304 --> 00:38:41,137
- Humph.

554
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:46,025
- [Sandra] Night, sweetheart.

555
00:38:46,025 --> 00:38:51,025
- [Shane] Goodnight, mom.

556
00:38:51,296 --> 00:38:54,296
(slow gentle music)

557
00:39:12,007 --> 00:39:15,340
(slow foreboding music)

558
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:58,608
- Hey, buddy, got a problem
under the hood there?

559
00:39:58,608 --> 00:40:01,171
- [Tommy] There you are,
where the hell you been?

560
00:40:01,171 --> 00:40:04,353
- Come on, let's see what you got, Tommy.

561
00:40:11,240 --> 00:40:12,073
- Check it out.

562
00:40:18,810 --> 00:40:21,143
- Looks like the genuine article to me.

563
00:40:22,119 --> 00:40:23,401
- You think that'll do?

564
00:40:23,401 --> 00:40:25,730
- [Leroy] Ought to.

565
00:40:25,730 --> 00:40:28,000
- We know the weeds there now,

566
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:29,510
but we don't know how long it's there for,

567
00:40:29,510 --> 00:40:31,350
so I think we ought to move fast.

568
00:40:31,350 --> 00:40:33,010
- I understand.

569
00:40:33,010 --> 00:40:35,700
- You know, 'cause I'm
kinda hangin' out on a limb

570
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:37,570
with this thing here, Leroy.

571
00:40:37,570 --> 00:40:38,760
You know, Caldwell's got--

572
00:40:38,760 --> 00:40:40,953
- He's got a sale with his name on it.

573
00:40:42,430 --> 00:40:43,440
Look, don't you worry none.

574
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:48,440
This is between you, me, and
the narc squad, all right?

575
00:40:50,121 --> 00:40:50,954
- All right.

576
00:40:56,510 --> 00:40:58,693
- [Sam] Gentlemen, we have a problem.

577
00:41:00,720 --> 00:41:01,553
Sheriff.

578
00:41:04,060 --> 00:41:06,160
- You're up to your ass in river mud, boy.

579
00:41:11,371 --> 00:41:12,690
- Hmm, what do you mean?

580
00:41:12,690 --> 00:41:15,173
- Your damn barrels of
weed, that's what I mean.

581
00:41:16,551 --> 00:41:17,950
Hell, you left a trail so wide,

582
00:41:17,950 --> 00:41:19,996
a blind coon dog could follow it.

583
00:41:19,996 --> 00:41:22,163
(wheezes)

584
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:24,713
- What happened?

585
00:41:26,070 --> 00:41:26,903
- What happened?

586
00:41:29,750 --> 00:41:33,630
Somebody told the police about
your little old schoolhouse.

587
00:41:33,630 --> 00:41:34,580
- Oh no, come on now.

588
00:41:34,580 --> 00:41:36,300
You sure, I helped
Mitchell unload that stuff,

589
00:41:36,300 --> 00:41:38,030
wasn't anybody around.

590
00:41:38,030 --> 00:41:40,850
- Well, welcome to the graveyard, boy.

591
00:41:40,850 --> 00:41:42,500
They start poking,

592
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:45,003
one old skeleton is gonna
lead right to another.

593
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:47,113
- Harris?

594
00:41:50,560 --> 00:41:51,500
- I didn't, uh--

595
00:41:51,500 --> 00:41:53,830
- You didn't think,
that's what you didn't do.

596
00:41:53,830 --> 00:41:56,450
You were careless and you were stupid.

597
00:41:56,450 --> 00:41:57,283
- Sam, if there's a--

598
00:41:57,283 --> 00:41:58,403
- [Sam] Don't Sam me!

599
00:42:00,310 --> 00:42:01,180
- Yes, sir.

600
00:42:02,050 --> 00:42:03,733
- I don like unhappy workers.

601
00:42:04,763 --> 00:42:06,430
I wanna know who talked, I wanna know why,

602
00:42:06,430 --> 00:42:07,623
and I wanna it stopped.

603
00:42:08,968 --> 00:42:11,732
(thunder roars)

604
00:42:11,732 --> 00:42:14,649
(slow tense music)

605
00:42:25,940 --> 00:42:27,390
- Sure this is where he said?

606
00:42:28,480 --> 00:42:29,330
- Yeah, I'm sure.

607
00:42:35,604 --> 00:42:37,553
Well, here, ask him yourself.

608
00:42:44,203 --> 00:42:46,260
What's going on?

609
00:42:46,260 --> 00:42:47,893
- Forget about Caldwell, Tommy.

610
00:42:48,929 --> 00:42:49,879
He's not touchable.

611
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:55,110
- What are you saying?

612
00:42:55,110 --> 00:42:57,240
- The investigation's closed.

613
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:59,197
The evidence is gone.

614
00:42:59,197 --> 00:43:00,340
- What?

615
00:43:00,340 --> 00:43:03,523
- I'm out of it, Tommy,
been pulled off the case.

616
00:43:04,751 --> 00:43:07,230
- Well, great, that's great.

617
00:43:07,230 --> 00:43:08,330
So they know about me?

618
00:43:09,210 --> 00:43:11,123
- Not by me, that's for damn sure.

619
00:43:12,050 --> 00:43:14,610
But I tell you, if they sniff me out,

620
00:43:14,610 --> 00:43:15,963
they could get to you too.

621
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:20,660
So if I was y'all, I'd just
forget this whole damn thing.

622
00:43:20,660 --> 00:43:23,283
Lay low and keep quiet
till this thing blows over.

623
00:43:37,550 --> 00:43:40,582
- Damn, thing's not gonna blow over.

624
00:43:40,582 --> 00:43:42,520
- No, it's not.

625
00:43:42,520 --> 00:43:45,607
- Just lay low and forget
about the whole thing?

626
00:43:47,076 --> 00:43:50,076
- Well, I tell ya, if we keep going,

627
00:43:51,770 --> 00:43:53,623
we won't have anywhere to go for help.

628
00:43:57,237 --> 00:43:58,070
- I know.

629
00:44:02,600 --> 00:44:03,433
- Why us?

630
00:44:04,834 --> 00:44:07,344
I mean we're just a weekly.

631
00:44:07,344 --> 00:44:09,080
The Constitution, they're a daily.

632
00:44:09,080 --> 00:44:11,730
They're big, they got teeth.

633
00:44:11,730 --> 00:44:13,299
- We tried that.

634
00:44:13,299 --> 00:44:15,150
We talked to some guy,
next thing you know,

635
00:44:15,150 --> 00:44:17,064
he's transferred out of state.

636
00:44:17,064 --> 00:44:18,314
- Could be a coincidence.

637
00:44:19,840 --> 00:44:21,140
- You really believe that?

638
00:44:23,560 --> 00:44:25,260
- We didn't know where else to go.

639
00:44:26,580 --> 00:44:28,630
We have plenty more where this came from.

640
00:44:31,430 --> 00:44:34,940
- Why not just take it to the police?

641
00:44:34,940 --> 00:44:36,424
- Already did.

642
00:44:36,424 --> 00:44:37,320
- [Albert] And?

643
00:44:37,320 --> 00:44:38,503
- Caldwell got to him.

644
00:44:41,710 --> 00:44:44,260
- David we'll need to have
access to other sources.

645
00:44:45,210 --> 00:44:46,160
- We'll arrange it.

646
00:44:47,439 --> 00:44:50,460
- All right, I'll try to
protect you and the sources,

647
00:44:50,460 --> 00:44:51,710
but there's no guarantee.

648
00:44:53,061 --> 00:44:55,437
- You know Caldwell better than I do,

649
00:44:55,437 --> 00:44:57,693
how do you think he'd react to all this?

650
00:44:58,730 --> 00:45:01,853
Remember, Georgia has swamps.

651
00:45:02,792 --> 00:45:05,292
- Well, sources have been
known to just disappear.

652
00:45:10,544 --> 00:45:12,627
- We'll take our chances.

653
00:45:14,330 --> 00:45:16,230
- [Beth] I can't, Sandra.

654
00:45:16,230 --> 00:45:18,400
- [Sandra] He promises
he won't use your name.

655
00:45:18,400 --> 00:45:19,950
- That won't stop
Caldwell from finding out,

656
00:45:19,950 --> 00:45:21,240
it'll just slow him down.

657
00:45:21,240 --> 00:45:23,840
- Beth, by the time he finds
out, it'll be too late.

658
00:45:25,978 --> 00:45:27,478
- I can't, Sandra.

659
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:32,540
- Beth, remember that night how you felt?

660
00:45:32,540 --> 00:45:34,130
Remember when I came to
see you in the hospital,

661
00:45:34,130 --> 00:45:36,230
Theresa didn't almost have a momma at all.

662
00:45:40,986 --> 00:45:42,836
- I just wanna make it up to Theresa.

663
00:45:45,018 --> 00:45:47,890
I wanna be a good mother.

664
00:45:47,890 --> 00:45:49,750
- I don't want my kids
growing up in a world

665
00:45:49,750 --> 00:45:52,560
where people like Caldwell
can do whatever they wanna do,

666
00:45:52,560 --> 00:45:54,770
and everybody's too scared
to even say anything.

667
00:45:54,770 --> 00:45:56,070
- It's right to be scared.

668
00:45:59,600 --> 00:46:01,500
- Beth, Tommy and I are gonna do this.

669
00:46:02,368 --> 00:46:03,683
We can't do it alone.

670
00:46:09,362 --> 00:46:10,612
- I don't know.

671
00:46:14,182 --> 00:46:17,265
(slow subdued music)

672
00:46:19,290 --> 00:46:20,690
- [Sandra] Just talk to him.

673
00:46:30,570 --> 00:46:32,770
- [Beth] Each office has at least one,

674
00:46:32,770 --> 00:46:34,903
always young, always attractive.

675
00:46:37,200 --> 00:46:39,093
They use them to win new friends,

676
00:46:40,500 --> 00:46:42,173
and blackmail and reward.

677
00:46:43,230 --> 00:46:45,480
They pass women around
like a piece of candy.

678
00:46:47,470 --> 00:46:50,640
Caldwell has a special
place up in Harriet's Bluff

679
00:46:50,640 --> 00:46:52,820
where he invites his female employees

680
00:46:52,820 --> 00:46:55,343
to entertain high-ranking officials.

681
00:46:57,210 --> 00:46:59,913
This isn't an isolated incident.

682
00:47:00,896 --> 00:47:05,896
It's almost common practice.

683
00:47:09,515 --> 00:47:13,015
- That ought to grab Caldwell's attention.

684
00:47:14,140 --> 00:47:15,363
- They can't do this.

685
00:47:16,500 --> 00:47:19,410
- [Attorney] Oh, it's
called freedom of the press.

686
00:47:19,410 --> 00:47:22,730
- Freedom, my ass, I'll shut 'em down.

687
00:47:22,730 --> 00:47:25,860
- Try it, you'll give them
an even bigger headline.

688
00:47:25,860 --> 00:47:28,693
- Well, hell, it's just
some two-bit podunk rag.

689
00:47:31,410 --> 00:47:34,790
- Sam, it'll all blow over.

690
00:47:36,063 --> 00:47:38,630
Now as your attorney,
my advice, let it be.

691
00:47:38,630 --> 00:47:41,410
- Well, my advice is
sue 'em, do something,

692
00:47:41,410 --> 00:47:44,430
find out where this
dribble is coming from.

693
00:47:44,430 --> 00:47:46,580
I'll be damned if I'm
just gonna let it be.

694
00:47:50,482 --> 00:47:52,628
(camera clicks)

695
00:47:52,628 --> 00:47:54,950
- [Man] Howdy, senator.

696
00:47:54,950 --> 00:47:56,040
- [Bo] I really appreciate

697
00:47:56,040 --> 00:47:57,803
these labor department volunteers.

698
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:00,730
- [Sam] Now they are gonna make you

699
00:48:00,730 --> 00:48:03,787
the best known face in Georgia, Bo

700
00:48:03,787 --> 00:48:06,426
- [Bo] Are you sure, Commissioner?

701
00:48:06,426 --> 00:48:09,308
- Oh, well, maybe, maybe
the second best known face.

702
00:48:09,308 --> 00:48:10,141
(camera clicks)

703
00:48:10,141 --> 00:48:11,940
Now Harris, we're not gonna read

704
00:48:11,940 --> 00:48:14,740
about this in the newspaper, now are we?

705
00:48:14,740 --> 00:48:17,540
- [Harris] Sam, you couldn't
find this place with a map.

706
00:48:20,450 --> 00:48:25,390
- Uh, how many people knew about your work

707
00:48:25,390 --> 00:48:27,453
on Bo Denton's campaign?

708
00:48:32,274 --> 00:48:35,163
- Maybe 20, Commissioner.

709
00:48:36,667 --> 00:48:39,393
- Hell, Sam, could be more
than one rooster crowing.

710
00:48:41,580 --> 00:48:44,320
- I'm not in the could be business.

711
00:48:44,320 --> 00:48:49,113
- Well, I'd say whoever he
is, he's inside the coop.

712
00:48:50,810 --> 00:48:52,823
He knows where the eggs are.

713
00:48:58,430 --> 00:49:02,363
- Well, sir, I could
make a guess if I had to.

714
00:49:04,531 --> 00:49:06,263
- Well, you have to, so guess.

715
00:49:07,931 --> 00:49:11,098
(slow gripping music)

716
00:49:58,110 --> 00:50:00,693
(Tommy grunts)

717
00:50:07,463 --> 00:50:08,803
- It's only a message.

718
00:50:10,310 --> 00:50:12,773
If they were sure, I'd be dead.

719
00:50:17,620 --> 00:50:21,675
- At least we know they read The Gazette.

720
00:50:21,675 --> 00:50:24,523
- Gotta feed The Gazette
at least one more story.

721
00:50:25,570 --> 00:50:27,120
Otherwise they'll know it's me.

722
00:50:29,610 --> 00:50:31,960
- Next time it won't be
just a message will it?

723
00:50:33,800 --> 00:50:38,023
- No, at least it doesn't
look like they suspect you.

724
00:50:38,930 --> 00:50:40,053
- [Shane] What happened?

725
00:50:40,970 --> 00:50:44,423
- Uh, I had a little fire at my apartment.

726
00:50:45,950 --> 00:50:46,783
It's okay.

727
00:50:50,940 --> 00:50:52,490
- Didn't exactly hide 'em, mom.

728
00:50:54,020 --> 00:50:55,520
I heard you talking with Beth.

729
00:50:58,239 --> 00:51:00,739
(phone rings)

730
00:51:02,450 --> 00:51:03,283
- Hello?

731
00:51:03,283 --> 00:51:06,222
- [Man] Lucky you weren't
in bed with your boyfriend.

732
00:51:06,222 --> 00:51:07,222
Look out the window.

733
00:51:16,824 --> 00:51:18,928
- [Shane] Leave my mom's car alone!

734
00:51:18,928 --> 00:51:22,105
- Shane!

735
00:51:22,105 --> 00:51:27,105
- [Shane] Get outta here, leave us alone!

736
00:51:32,623 --> 00:51:34,873
- [Sandra] Shane, oh, baby.

737
00:51:38,335 --> 00:51:39,502
You all right?

738
00:51:53,807 --> 00:51:56,724
(slow tense music)

739
00:52:23,947 --> 00:52:25,747
- [Shannon] Why are we in Tommy's car?

740
00:52:26,820 --> 00:52:28,040
Where's our car?

741
00:52:28,040 --> 00:52:29,600
- Somebody hit it last night, honey.

742
00:52:29,600 --> 00:52:30,800
We'll have it back soon.

743
00:52:32,766 --> 00:52:33,599
Tommy.

744
00:52:33,599 --> 00:52:34,766
- [Tommy] Hmm?

745
00:52:43,160 --> 00:52:45,088
- [Sandra] Y'all want hamburger?

746
00:52:45,088 --> 00:52:47,755
- [Shannon] I'm not hungry, mom.

747
00:53:03,311 --> 00:53:04,330
- Let's see if he stops.

748
00:53:04,330 --> 00:53:05,163
- [Sandra] Mm hmm.

749
00:53:06,910 --> 00:53:09,463
- Yep, he's stopping.

750
00:53:11,720 --> 00:53:13,180
All right, now, Shane.

751
00:53:13,180 --> 00:53:14,013
- [Shane] Huh?

752
00:53:14,013 --> 00:53:15,570
- You wanna get me a root beer?

753
00:53:15,570 --> 00:53:16,820
- [Shane] Oh, I thought we
were gonna go get hamburger.

754
00:53:16,820 --> 00:53:19,133
- [Sandra] Honey, just come on, get out.

755
00:53:19,133 --> 00:53:19,966
- [Shane] Well, why?

756
00:53:19,966 --> 00:53:20,920
- [Tommy] Come on, get up darling.

757
00:53:20,920 --> 00:53:22,585
- [Sandra] Sweetheart, you
wanna go to the ladies' room?

758
00:53:22,585 --> 00:53:23,790
- [Shannon] Do we have to?

759
00:53:23,790 --> 00:53:24,918
- [Tommy] No backtalk, darlin'.

760
00:53:24,918 --> 00:53:26,701
- [Sandra] Yes, darlin' we do.

761
00:53:26,701 --> 00:53:27,618
Here we go.

762
00:53:54,953 --> 00:53:56,243
- Hold it right there.

763
00:54:01,350 --> 00:54:02,627
Now mister, I don't know who
you are or what you want,

764
00:54:02,627 --> 00:54:04,393
but I got a good shot at you.

765
00:54:05,596 --> 00:54:09,204
- Take it easy, Mr.
Marchant, I'm a friend.

766
00:54:09,204 --> 00:54:11,621
(gun clicks)

767
00:54:13,690 --> 00:54:15,873
- Come forward, put your
hands here on the hood.

768
00:54:25,210 --> 00:54:28,433
- My name is John
Curtis, I'm with the FBI.

769
00:54:30,066 --> 00:54:31,466
- And how would I know that?

770
00:54:33,000 --> 00:54:36,980
- Look, I'm gonna move my hands real slow.

771
00:54:36,980 --> 00:54:40,283
I'm gonna open my coat
and show you my badge.

772
00:54:43,845 --> 00:54:45,900
And you're gonna put that gun away,

773
00:54:45,900 --> 00:54:47,073
and we're gonna talk.

774
00:54:55,420 --> 00:54:56,513
Interesting reading.

775
00:54:58,120 --> 00:55:00,070
If even half of this stuff
could be made to stick,

776
00:55:00,070 --> 00:55:02,833
these boys will go away
for a long, long time.

777
00:55:03,885 --> 00:55:05,233
- How'd you find us?

778
00:55:06,230 --> 00:55:08,783
- Hey, we're the FBI.

779
00:55:10,130 --> 00:55:11,170
- Yeah, but if you can figure it out,

780
00:55:11,170 --> 00:55:12,093
so can Caldwell.

781
00:55:13,750 --> 00:55:15,950
- Yeah, I heard they
tried to smoke you out.

782
00:55:17,840 --> 00:55:20,270
Seems like you all could use some help.

783
00:55:20,270 --> 00:55:21,643
- Why should we trust you?

784
00:55:23,350 --> 00:55:26,853
- Frankly, I don't think
