873
01:01:32,674 --> 01:01:33,507
Hi, darlin'.

874
01:01:37,070 --> 01:01:38,860
- Well, a couple of fine
looking kids you got here.

875
01:01:38,860 --> 01:01:40,309
You enjoying your dinner?

876
01:01:40,309 --> 01:01:41,142
Are you?

877
01:01:41,142 --> 01:01:41,988
- What do you say?

878
01:01:41,988 --> 01:01:42,821
- All right.

879
01:01:42,821 --> 01:01:44,529
Fine looking boy, too, how are you?

880
01:01:44,529 --> 01:01:45,362
- Shane.

881
01:01:45,362 --> 01:01:46,195
- Yeah.

882
01:01:46,195 --> 01:01:47,157
- [MC] Let's give a round of applause

883
01:01:47,157 --> 01:01:48,803
for Commissioner Sam Caldwell.

884
01:01:50,269 --> 01:01:51,272
Come on, everybody.

885
01:01:51,272 --> 01:01:55,189
(audience cheers and applauds)

886
01:02:01,846 --> 01:02:02,846
- Hi, sugar.

887
01:02:05,901 --> 01:02:08,151
- Good crowd, lots of food.

888
01:02:09,560 --> 01:02:11,693
- Well, I didn't come here to eat, honey.

889
01:02:12,650 --> 01:02:13,747
- Good evening, ladies and gentlemen,

890
01:02:13,747 --> 01:02:16,503
thank you for that warm reception.

891
01:02:17,740 --> 01:02:19,840
Thank you all for coming out here tonight.

892
01:02:20,820 --> 01:02:23,260
- Why don't we go jump in a lake, huh?

893
01:02:24,231 --> 01:02:27,437
- Listen darling, I'm
working, you know that.

894
01:02:27,437 --> 01:02:29,587
- How come you don't
ever wanna work on me?

895
01:02:32,548 --> 01:02:35,120
I bet we could get your mind on something

896
01:02:35,120 --> 01:02:37,520
a little more interesting
than all those trucks.

897
01:02:38,414 --> 01:02:41,262
(gasps) Oh no, silly ole me.

898
01:02:41,262 --> 01:02:42,363
Oh, look what I done.

899
01:02:43,400 --> 01:02:44,452
Oh, you're all wet.

900
01:02:44,452 --> 01:02:45,498
- That's all right, come on.

901
01:02:45,498 --> 01:02:48,240
- [Melissa] Oh, my,
my, all the drying off.

