01:03:09,360 --> 01:03:10,990
didn't come here for the food,

911
01:03:10,990 --> 01:03:12,500
and I've already heard the Caldwell talk,

912
01:03:12,500 --> 01:03:14,863
so why don't we go for that swim?

913
01:03:20,181 --> 01:03:24,098
(audience cheers and applauds)

914
01:03:43,129 --> 01:03:46,046
(car engine whirs)

915
01:03:54,574 --> 01:03:57,324
(car door slams)

916
01:04:03,714 --> 01:04:06,631
(knocking on door)

917
01:04:15,542 --> 01:04:16,792
- Hey, it's me.

918
01:04:18,230 --> 01:04:19,063
- Oh.

919
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:28,253
Hot date, huh?

920
01:04:30,460 --> 01:04:32,393
- Well, I don't know
if I'd call it a date.

921
01:04:34,690 --> 01:04:36,897
- What would you call it?

922
01:04:36,897 --> 01:04:38,060
The last time I saw

923
01:04:38,060 --> 01:04:40,060
you were pretty wrapped up in your work.

924
01:04:41,720 --> 01:04:43,300
- Yeah, well, I figured I had a choice.

925
01:04:43,300 --> 01:04:45,370
You know, here I'd take Melissa out,

926
01:04:45,370 --> 01:04:48,957
or Mitchell will take me out, permanently.

927
01:04:52,890 --> 01:04:54,610
- She didn't find the wire, did she?

928
01:04:54,610 --> 01:04:56,830
- Well, yeah, she might of seen something.

929
01:04:56,830 --> 01:05:00,070
But she's so drunk I don't
think she'll remember, you know.

930
01:05:00,070 --> 01:05:02,423
I mean she passed out
before I got her home.

931
01:05:05,350 --> 01:05:06,500
I took her mind off it.

932
01:05:10,980 --> 01:05:12,990
- See if we can take your mind off her.

933
01:05:22,657 --> 01:05:24,407
- Yeah, that'll help.

934
01:05:35,537 --> 01:05:37,120
- You can't go back into work.

935
01:05:38,239 --> 01:05:39,720
- No, I gotta go right back in.

936
01:05:39,720 --> 01:05:42,400
I gotta go in like nothing
happened whatsoever.

937
01:05:42,400 --> 01:05:47,400
- You can't, what if Melissa
wasn't really so drunk?

938
01:05:49,603 --> 01:05:50,903
What if she does remember?

939
01:05:57,075 --> 01:05:58,242
- [Tommy] Yep.

940
01:06:07,260 --> 01:06:10,343
(slow intense music)

941
01:06:29,620 --> 01:06:32,120
(men chatter)

942
01:06:39,880 --> 01:06:43,099
- [Mitchell] I said let's go.

943
01:06:43,099 --> 01:06:45,599
In the car bigmouth, let's go.

944
01:07:19,281 --> 01:07:20,300
- [Man] FBI.

945
01:07:20,300 --> 01:07:22,790
- I need to speak to Special
Agent Curtis, please.

946
01:07:22,790 --> 01:07:26,630
- [Man] Special Agent Curtis
is not available just now.

947
01:07:26,630 --> 01:07:27,814
Would you care to leave a
number where he could reach you?

948
01:07:27,814 --> 01:07:28,647
- Sandra?

949
01:07:30,150 --> 01:07:32,300
Honey, don't you have
a phone at your desk?

950
01:07:34,740 --> 01:07:37,400
You know we're having a
little party next week,

951
01:07:37,400 --> 01:07:40,440
and Mr. Wiley would like me
to be sure that you're there.

952
01:07:40,440 --> 01:07:42,890
Now you don't wanna put
me in a bad light do you?

953
01:07:44,304 --> 01:07:47,221
(slow tense music)

954
01:08:11,430 --> 01:08:14,097
- All right, get out of the car.

955
01:08:16,145 --> 01:08:17,728
You wanted to talk?

956
01:08:19,962 --> 01:08:20,879
Let's talk.

957
01:08:30,787 --> 01:08:33,704
(Melissa chuckles)

958
01:08:58,943 --> 01:09:00,863
- You got a big mouth, Tommy.

959
01:09:03,010 --> 01:09:05,590
- You knew about the marijuana, Harris,

960
01:09:05,590 --> 01:09:07,010
and the women and the tobacco barn,

961
01:09:07,010 --> 01:09:08,843
maybe it was you, maybe it was Mitch.

962
01:09:10,270 --> 01:09:11,733
- No, it was you, Tommy.

963
01:09:13,850 --> 01:09:15,810
Melissa saw the wire.

964
01:09:15,810 --> 01:09:17,700
- What wire, she saw nothin'.

965
01:09:17,700 --> 01:09:19,027
All right, she's got the hots for me,

966
01:09:19,027 --> 01:09:19,860
you all know that,

967
01:09:19,860 --> 01:09:21,380
and she was all over me last night.

968
01:09:21,380 --> 01:09:22,850
She got mad when I said no.

969
01:09:22,850 --> 01:09:23,830
- She wouldn't lie to me.

970
01:09:23,830 --> 01:09:26,360
- Well, she did, okay.

971
01:09:26,360 --> 01:09:27,870
She wanted to get even with me.

972
01:09:27,870 --> 01:09:29,270
She was drunk and that's it.

973
01:09:32,588 --> 01:09:34,570
You know, Sam's gonna love this.

974
01:09:34,570 --> 01:09:36,200
You kill me, he gets murder one.

975
01:09:36,200 --> 01:09:37,763
And your deep throat?

976
01:09:38,890 --> 01:09:39,740
Keeps on talking.

977
01:09:50,640 --> 01:09:52,190
- Better stop right there, boy.

978
01:09:56,430 --> 01:09:57,380
- I got work to do.

979
01:10:00,430 --> 01:10:02,880
- Okay, Mitch, put it away.

980
01:10:54,173 --> 01:10:55,923
- Scared me to death.

981
01:10:57,684 --> 01:10:58,977
You could've got yourself killed.

982
01:10:58,977 --> 01:10:59,810
- I'm okay.

983
01:11:03,661 --> 01:11:06,210
- I just don't ever wanna lose you.

984
01:11:19,808 --> 01:11:22,280
(gun fires)

985
01:11:22,280 --> 01:11:23,180
Kicks like a mule.

986
01:11:24,580 --> 01:11:27,916
- Yeah, all right, move
a little further forward.

987
01:11:27,916 --> 01:11:31,107
All right, relax your
arms a little bit too.

988
01:11:31,107 --> 01:11:33,043
Loosen them up a little bit.

989
01:11:33,043 --> 01:11:35,376
Okay, what are you gonna do?

990
01:11:36,373 --> 01:11:38,373
Exhale, squeeze slowly--

991
01:11:39,857 --> 01:11:41,212
- Honey, don't.

992
01:11:41,212 --> 01:11:42,295
- Don't pull.

993
01:11:43,845 --> 01:11:45,266
(gun fires)

994
01:11:45,266 --> 01:11:49,006
Beautiful, good shootin, Sundance.

995
01:11:49,006 --> 01:11:50,678
- Thank you.

996
01:11:50,678 --> 01:11:52,141
- Let's hope you never have to use it.

997
01:11:52,141 --> 01:11:56,251
- Yeah, but if I do, I
damn sure wanna know how.

998
01:11:56,251 --> 01:11:58,510
(guns fires)

999
01:11:58,510 --> 01:12:00,593
