01:16:37,870 --> 01:16:40,752
Labor Commissioner Sam
Caldwell on fraud charges.

1070
01:16:40,752 --> 01:16:41,585
- [Tommy] Nice!

1071
01:16:41,585 --> 01:16:42,418
(Sandra laughs)

1072
01:16:42,418 --> 01:16:43,730
- [Brian] The eight count
indictment is the result

1073
01:16:43,730 --> 01:16:45,290
of an ongoing investigation

1074
01:16:45,290 --> 01:16:46,910
which began when The Georgia Gazette

1075
01:16:46,910 --> 01:16:48,550
reported widespread corruption

1076
01:16:48,550 --> 01:16:50,290
inside the Department of Labor.

1077
01:16:50,290 --> 01:16:52,018
A trail is to expected
to begin next month.

1078
01:16:52,018 --> 01:16:53,087
(Shane and Tommy shout)

1079
01:16:53,087 --> 01:16:55,748
(phone rings)

1080
01:16:55,748 --> 01:16:59,081
(all chatter excitedly)

1081
01:17:02,254 --> 01:17:03,171
- How, how?

1082
01:17:06,850 --> 01:17:07,923
Fine, all right.

1083
01:17:09,151 --> 01:17:11,023
I understand, we'll call you back.

1084
01:17:13,450 --> 01:17:15,153
- Sandra, what do you think of that?

1085
01:17:19,969 --> 01:17:20,802
What's wrong?

1086
01:17:20,802 --> 01:17:21,635
- Curtis.

1087
01:17:25,423 --> 01:17:26,423
- What is it?

1088
01:17:28,083 --> 01:17:29,916
- There's been a leak.

1089
01:17:30,758 --> 01:17:32,591
They know who you are.

1090
01:17:37,223 --> 01:17:38,056
(reporters chatter)

1091
01:17:38,056 --> 01:17:40,650
- Mr. Caldwell.
- Mr. Caldwell.

1092
01:17:40,650 --> 01:17:42,450
- [Reporter] Do you plan to resign, sir?

1093
01:17:42,450 --> 01:17:45,680
- I'm confident that a jury
will clear my good name

1094
01:17:45,680 --> 01:17:46,817
and now, ladies and gentlemen,

1095
01:17:46,817 --> 01:17:48,754
the job training bill needs me.

1096
01:17:48,754 --> 01:17:49,587
Excuse me.

1097
01:17:49,587 --> 01:17:51,110
- The Georgia Gazette
reported widespread--

1098
01:17:51,110 --> 01:17:53,800
- Georgia Gazette, don't
tell me you read that rag.

1099
01:17:53,800 --> 01:17:56,880
I, for one, am proud to say I read our own

1100
01:17:56,880 --> 01:17:58,253
Atlanta Constitution, thank you.

1101
01:17:58,253 --> 01:18:00,620
- [Reporter] Well, what
about Mr. Marchant, sir?

1102
01:18:00,620 --> 01:18:03,350
- Mr. Marchant is a
disgruntled state employee,

1103
01:18:03,350 --> 01:18:05,480
and I may add a liar.

1104
01:18:05,480 --> 01:18:08,410
And as of today, Mr.
Marchant no longer works

1105
01:18:08,410 --> 01:18:10,689
for the Georgia Department
of Labor, please--

1106
01:18:10,689 --> 01:18:11,522
- [Man In White Shirt]
Commissioner, commissioner--

1107
01:18:11,522 --> 01:18:12,870
- Young man, if I were you,

1108
01:18:12,870 --> 01:18:14,498
I'd get outta my way!

1109
01:18:14,498 --> 01:18:16,900
(reporters chatter)

1110
01:18:16,900 --> 01:18:19,563
- It seems that somebody
planted a bug in my office.

1111
01:18:20,740 --> 01:18:21,573
You know who?

1112
01:18:23,560 --> 01:18:24,393
- No, sir.

1113
01:18:27,320 --> 01:18:29,110
- It also seems that Tommy Marchant

1114
01:18:29,110 --> 01:18:30,873
testified before the grand jury.

1115
01:18:32,248 --> 01:18:33,081
- He did?

1116
01:18:34,780 --> 01:18:37,280
Well, what does that got
to do with me, Mr. Wiley?

1117
01:18:40,460 --> 01:18:44,960
- I know that you and
Tommy are close friends.

1118
01:18:44,960 --> 01:18:47,347
- Yes, sir, I have a number
of close friends, so?

1119
01:18:51,460 --> 01:18:53,580
- Atlanta just slashed my budget.

1120
01:18:53,580 --> 01:18:55,030
I'm gonna have to let you go.

1121
01:18:56,580 --> 01:18:59,070
- I really need this job, Mr. Wiley.

1122
01:18:59,070 --> 01:19:01,923
- Doesn't have to be like this, you know.

1123
01:19:01,923 --> 01:19:02,756
- [Sandra] No?

1124
01:19:02,756 --> 01:19:04,453
- No, you're a smart woman.

1125
01:19:07,370 --> 01:19:09,123
- Well, how smart do I have to be?

1126
01:19:10,210 --> 01:19:11,960
- Smart enough to be a team player.

1127
01:19:13,110 --> 01:19:15,010
- What's a team player expected to do?

1128
01:19:16,400 --> 01:19:18,110
- A team player's expected to care

1129
01:19:18,110 --> 01:19:20,560
about her boss, the commissioner.

1130
01:19:20,560 --> 01:19:23,810
A team player's expected
to testify for him

1131
01:19:23,810 --> 01:19:26,303
against Tommy Marchant
if push comes to shove.

1132
01:19:31,110 --> 01:19:33,438
- That's some very serious team playing.

1133
01:19:33,438 --> 01:19:34,271
- [Harris] Mm hmm.

1134
01:19:34,271 --> 01:19:35,871
- Can you let me think about it?

1135
01:19:37,890 --> 01:19:39,140
- Well, you do that then.

1136
01:19:45,960 --> 01:19:48,017
- I really need this job, Mr. Wiley.

1137
01:19:54,360 --> 01:19:56,640
You can't put it off any
longer, you gotta go.

1138
01:19:56,640 --> 01:19:57,600
- [Tommy] I'm not running.

1139
01:19:57,600 --> 01:19:59,010
- It's not running, Tommy.

1140
01:19:59,010 --> 01:20:00,420
They'll put you in a safe house.

1141
01:20:00,420 --> 01:20:02,900
- Yeah, where I can't call
you, can't see the kids.

1142
01:20:02,900 --> 01:20:03,733
- [Sandra] Tommy, please.

1143
01:20:03,733 --> 01:20:05,420
- And what if there's a leak in the FBI?

1144
01:20:05,420 --> 01:20:08,760
All right, I'm hiding out here in town.

1145
01:20:08,760 --> 01:20:10,024
- I want you safe.

1146
01:20:10,024 --> 01:20:11,501
- [Tommy] Well, I don't
wanna talk about it.

1147
01:20:11,501 --> 01:20:12,334
- Would you just listen.

1148
01:20:12,334 --> 01:20:14,003
- I don't wanna talk about it.

1149
01:20:15,151 --> 01:20:18,970
(slow subdued music)

1150
01:20:18,970 --> 01:20:20,863
- Why are you guys yelling?

1151
01:20:22,330 --> 01:20:23,800
It woke me up.

1152
01:20:23,800 --> 01:20:25,470
- Oh, sweetheart, come here.

1153
01:20:27,046 --> 01:20:28,796
Come here, I'm sorry.

1154
01:20:30,500 --> 01:20:33,110
- Sorry, darlin', didn't
mean to talk so loud.

1155
01:20:36,303 --> 01:20:39,445
- Are you gonna leave like daddy did?

1156
01:20:39,445 --> 01:20:40,612
- [Sandra] Oh.

1157
01:20:44,300 --> 01:20:45,533
- No, sweetheart.

1158
01:20:48,000 --> 01:20:50,967
- Tommy may have to go
away for a little while,

1159
01:20:50,967 --> 01:20:52,467
but he'll be back.

1160
01:20:53,497 --> 01:20:55,453
Back to bed, okay?

1161
01:20:55,453 --> 01:20:57,690
- Okay.

1162
01:20:57,690 --> 01:20:58,647
- Goodnight, Tommy.

1163
01:21:00,970 --> 01:21:02,970
- Goodnight, sweetheart.

1164
01:21:15,097 --> 01:21:16,180
- Hey, Tommy?

1165
01:21:21,144 --> 01:21:24,090
I just wanna say I'm
glad you're not gonna run

1166
01:21:24,090 --> 01:21:25,190
like mom wants you to.

1167
01:21:28,010 --> 01:21:32,593
- Shane, your mom's the
bravest person I ever met.

1168
01:21:35,617 --> 01:21:37,117
You must be very proud of her.

1169
01:21:40,062 --> 01:21:41,395
- Yeah, I guess.

1170
01:21:43,940 --> 01:21:47,080
- Shane, look, I'm no big hero.

1171
01:21:47,080 --> 01:21:48,550
Okay, I'm scared to death.

1172
01:21:48,550 --> 01:21:52,070
I know these boys, but if I
run like the FBI wants me to

1173
01:21:52,070 --> 01:21:54,073
I won't see your mom for a long time.

1174
01:21:58,085 --> 01:22:00,935
And I've been waiting for
someone like her my whole life.

1175
01:22:09,161 --> 01:22:11,661
I'm not gonna give her up now.

1176
01:22:12,860 --> 01:22:13,950
Simple as that.

1177
01:22:14,960 --> 01:22:15,793
- She know that?

1178
01:22:22,210 --> 01:22:23,260
- I believe she does.

1179
01:22:41,270 --> 01:22:42,883
- I've slept on it, Mr. Wiley.

1180
01:22:44,020 --> 01:22:45,720
You want me to testify

1181
01:22:45,720 --> 01:22:48,343
for Mr. Caldwell against Mr. Marchant.

1182
01:22:51,430 --> 01:22:52,860
- That's right.

1183
01:22:52,860 --> 01:22:54,653
- And if I do, I can keep my job.

1184
01:22:56,195 --> 01:22:57,028
- Correct.

1185
01:22:58,610 --> 01:23:01,740
- Well, it seems to me that
if I'm gonna join the team,

1186
01:23:01,740 --> 01:23:05,103
I ought to be awarded a position
of greater responsibility.

1187
01:23:08,316 --> 01:23:11,773
- (chuckles) Why Sandra,

1188
01:23:17,490 --> 01:23:22,003
well, I think you better call me Harris.

1189
01:23:23,630 --> 01:23:25,080
You're a tough woman, Sandra.

1190
01:23:26,160 --> 01:23:27,563
- Yes, I am, Harris.

1191
01:23:30,620 --> 01:23:35,383
- Well, I think I can
swing a promotion, yeah.

1192
01:23:37,130 --> 01:23:41,363
- And what do I say against
Tommy Marchant, Harris?

1193
01:23:44,440 --> 01:23:47,240
- I bet if you tried real hard,

1194
01:23:47,240 --> 01:23:48,340
I can't tell you what to say,

1195
01:23:48,340 --> 01:23:50,510
but if you tried real hard

1196
01:23:50,510 --> 01:23:53,070
I bet you could remember
something that said to you.

1197
01:23:53,070 --> 01:23:54,133
- Such as?

1198
01:23:57,940 --> 01:24:02,030
- Such as the time that Tommy Marchant

1199
01:24:02,030 --> 01:24:04,933
offered you a promotion in
return for sexual favors.

1200
01:24:11,030 --> 01:24:12,600
Or the time that Mr. Marchant

1201
01:24:12,600 --> 01:24:15,933
had you double bill the
state for per diem claims.

1202
01:24:18,290 --> 01:24:20,620
- I can't tell you what
pleasure this gives me.

1203
01:24:20,620 --> 01:24:22,040
I got him cold, didn't I?

1204
01:24:24,340 --> 01:24:25,173
What's wrong?

1205
01:24:27,180 --> 01:24:28,940
Something the matter with the tape?

1206
01:24:28,940 --> 01:24:30,540
- No, it's not the tape, Sandra.

1207
01:24:31,530 --> 01:24:35,078
We got a tip, there's a
contract out on Tommy.

1208
01:24:35,078 --> 01:24:37,660
(slow unsettling music)

1209
01:24:37,660 --> 01:24:40,100
You know, I can't protect
him if he won't come in.

1210
01:24:40,100 --> 01:24:41,660
- I'll get in touch with him.

1211
01:24:41,660 --> 01:24:43,660
- You think he'll listen?

1212
01:24:43,660 --> 01:24:45,536
- I don't know.

1213
01:24:45,536 --> 01:24:48,453
(slow tense music)

1214
01:25:48,369 --> 01:25:49,202
- [Sandra] You okay?

1215
01:25:49,202 --> 01:25:50,393
- [Tommy] Yeah, I'm having a ball.

1216
01:25:52,700 --> 01:25:54,321
- Curtis wants you to come in.

1217
01:25:54,321 --> 01:25:55,154
- Yeah?

1218
01:25:57,539 --> 01:26:00,956
(slow suspenseful music)

1219
01:26:02,185 --> 01:26:04,185
We had that talk before.

1220
01:26:05,050 --> 01:26:07,610
- Yeah, well, I guess we're
gonna have to have it again.

1221
01:26:07,610 --> 01:26:08,693
- Afraid not.

1222
01:26:11,426 --> 01:26:14,093
(shotgun fires)

1223
01:26:23,520 --> 01:26:25,960
Let's go, get in the car.

1224
01:26:25,960 --> 01:26:26,836
They must have followed you.

1225
01:26:26,836 --> 01:26:27,736
- Oh my God, the kids.

1226
01:26:27,736 --> 01:26:29,403
Tommy, get the kids.

1227
01:26:49,986 --> 01:26:52,243
I'll kill 'em if they hurt my babies.

1228
01:26:52,243 --> 01:26:53,826
- [Tommy] Let's go.

1229
01:27:04,949 --> 01:27:06,453
- Oh, sweetheart.

1230
01:27:06,453 --> 01:27:08,334
- [Tommy] Shane!

1231
01:27:08,334 --> 01:27:09,167
Shane!

1232
01:27:11,832 --> 01:27:14,435
- [Sandra] You're sleepy,
come back up here.

1233
01:27:14,435 --> 01:27:15,648
Jump up on your bed.

1234
01:27:15,648 --> 01:27:18,510
Let's get this around your shoulders.

1235
01:27:18,510 --> 01:27:21,190
- For God's sake, no
they took a shot at us.

1236
01:27:21,190 --> 01:27:22,440
Could have killed Sandra.

1237
01:27:24,276 --> 01:27:25,740
- I don't wanna go, I don't wanna go.

1238
01:27:25,740 --> 01:27:28,293
- Shannon, please, just
don't fuss, all right?

1239
01:27:29,570 --> 01:27:30,403
- [Tommy] No, we're going to Beth's.

1240
01:27:30,403 --> 01:27:32,260
- [Sandra] Move it, Shane, come on, baby.

1241
01:27:32,260 --> 01:27:33,093
- Right.

1242
01:27:34,150 --> 01:27:35,070
- [Shane] What are we doing?

1243
01:27:35,070 --> 01:27:36,924
What is going on?

1244
01:27:36,924 --> 01:27:41,924
- No, yeah, no they're
coming with us, both of them.

1245
01:27:42,320 --> 01:27:43,696
Of course, all right, go ahead, why not.

1246
01:27:43,696 --> 01:27:44,616
- [Sandra] Look out.

1247
01:27:44,616 --> 01:27:45,850
Here we go, up we go.

1248
01:27:45,850 --> 01:27:48,423
- [Tommy] Just tell
your men meet us there.

1249
01:27:52,018 --> 01:27:55,351
(police radio chatters)

1250
01:28:09,670 --> 01:28:12,170
- [Officer] Is everybody okay?

1251
01:28:16,649 --> 01:28:18,732
- [Tommy] Let's go on in.

1252
01:28:26,170 --> 01:28:27,120
- [John] They took a shot at you?

1253
01:28:27,120 --> 01:28:30,103
- Well, they're not
exactly a friendly bunch.

1254
01:28:33,290 --> 01:28:34,540
- She gonna be all right?

1255
01:28:36,458 --> 01:28:38,643
- You ever had to talk back to a shotgun?

1256
01:28:41,550 --> 01:28:44,963
- Look, Tommy, we need her testimony.

1257
01:28:47,200 --> 01:28:49,373
Without it we might as well just go home.

1258
01:28:51,756 --> 01:28:52,589
- I know.

1259
01:28:53,539 --> 01:28:56,548
- [John] Look, come on.

1260
01:28:56,548 --> 01:28:57,381
Sorry about--

1261
01:28:57,381 --> 01:28:58,345
- [Tommy] Oh, it's all right.

1262
01:28:58,345 --> 01:29:00,595
I appreciate you coming in.

1263
01:29:04,843 --> 01:29:06,660
- Mom, don't worry, okay.

1264
01:29:06,660 --> 01:29:09,233
I'll take care of Shannon,
everything will be okay.

1265
01:29:12,389 --> 01:29:14,989
- I know I'm the last person
to lecture you, Sandra.

1266
01:29:15,930 --> 01:29:17,530
- If I testify they could...

1267
01:29:21,120 --> 01:29:23,323
It's not me I'm worried about.

1268
01:29:25,410 --> 01:29:26,260
- Go for it, mom.

1269
01:29:30,390 --> 01:29:32,323
- Could go on for a long time, honey.

1270
01:29:38,150 --> 01:29:38,983
- Remember when you came

1271
01:29:38,983 --> 01:29:40,700
and talked to me about that reporter?

1272
01:29:43,740 --> 01:29:45,640
I remember that night at the hospital.

1273
01:29:47,830 --> 01:29:48,663
I remember.

1274
01:29:52,650 --> 01:29:54,650
My daughter's never gonna feel that way.

1275
01:30:03,280 --> 01:30:04,680
Do it for your kids, Sandra.

1276
01:30:16,200 --> 01:30:17,033
- I love you.

1277
01:30:19,591 --> 01:30:20,924
Thank you, Beth.

1278
01:30:31,023 --> 01:30:33,563
- Will you state your name
for the record, please.

1279
01:30:35,700 --> 01:30:37,243
- My name is Sandra Clayton.

1280
01:30:39,770 --> 01:30:42,730
- And Miss Clayton,
could you tell this court

1281
01:30:42,730 --> 01:30:45,730
what position you hold with the
Georgia Department of Labor?

1282
01:30:48,290 --> 01:30:49,833
- I am a secretary.

1283
01:30:52,370 --> 01:30:56,033
- Are you acquainted with the
defendant, Mr. Sam Caldwell?

1284
01:31:06,660 --> 01:31:07,493
- Yes.

1285
01:31:09,360 --> 01:31:12,943
(mid-tempo dramatic music)

1286
01:31:19,670 --> 01:31:21,922
- [Beth] Come on, come on, come on, honey.

1287
01:31:21,922 --> 01:31:23,563
Everyone, everyone, a toast.

1288
01:31:25,170 --> 01:31:29,263
To Tommy and Sandra, my best
friends, may stardust fall.

1289
01:31:30,374 --> 01:31:32,127
- [All] Cheers.

1290
01:31:32,127 --> 01:31:35,294
(slow delicate music)

1291
01:31:36,754 --> 01:31:38,745
- [Tommy] Are we ready to cut this thing?

1292
01:31:38,745 --> 01:31:40,309
